            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Package repo</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
              iOS SDK source, <code>Package.swift</code>, examples, tests, and release notes live in <code>logister-ios</code>. The Rails app stores project setup, API keys, platform import settings, and received telemetry.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
            Package repo:
            <%= link_to "logister-ios",
                        "https://github.com/taimoorq/logister-ios",
                        target: "_blank",
                        rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                        class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 no-underline font-semibold" %>.
            Release:
            <%= link_to "v0.1.1",
                        "https://github.com/taimoorq/logister-ios/releases/tag/v0.1.1",
                        target: "_blank",
                        rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                        class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 no-underline font-semibold" %>.
          </p>
        </div>
      <% elsif @project.integration_http_api? %>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Best path</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Generate a project API key and store it in the sending app, script, or service.</li>
              <li>POST JSON to <code>/api/v1/ingest_events</code> with <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code> or <code>X-Api-Key: &lt;token&gt;</code>.</li>
              <li>Use <code>event_type</code> values such as <code>error</code>, <code>log</code>, <code>metric</code>, <code>transaction</code>, <code>span</code>, and <code>check_in</code>.</li>
              <li>Send stable <code>environment</code>, <code>release</code>, <code>trace_id</code>, and <code>request_id</code> fields when you have them so Logister can filter and correlate events.</li>
              <li>Use <code>/api/v1/check_ins</code> for cron jobs and scheduled tasks when you only need monitor heartbeats.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Start with cURL</h3>
            <pre class="<%= project_setup_code_block_class %>"><code>curl -X POST https://your-logister-host.example/api/v1/ingest_events \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-project-api-token" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "event": {
      "event_type": "error",
      "level": "error",
      "message": "Unhandled exception in CheckoutService",
      "fingerprint": "checkout-unhandled-exception",
      "context": {
        "environment": "production",
        "release": "2026.05.23",
        "service": "checkout-api"
      }
    }
  }'</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">API tooling</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
              Use the HTTP API guide for payload examples, the Swagger API reference for the OpenAPI contract, or import the Postman collection when you want ready-made requests for every supported event family.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
            Public setup guide:
            <%= link_to "HTTP API docs", docs_site_url(:http_api), target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 no-underline font-semibold" %>.
            API contract:
            <%= link_to "Swagger / OpenAPI reference", docs_site_url(:api_reference), target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 no-underline font-semibold" %>.
          </p>
        </div>
      <% else %>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Best path</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Install the <code>logister-ruby</code> gem in the Rails app you want to monitor.</li>
              <li>Configure the project API token and ingest endpoint in the initializer.</li>
              <li>Enable database metrics and <code>capture_request_spans</code> if you want request load waterfall charts in the performance view.</li>
              <li>Set <code>LOGISTER_REPOSITORY</code>, <code>LOGISTER_COMMIT_SHA</code>, and <code>LOGISTER_BRANCH</code> so source-aware error detail can resolve frames to the right code.</li>
              <li>Call <code>Logister.record_deployment</code> from CI/CD after a deploy so release history links back to the deployed commit.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Start with</h3>
            <pre class="<%= project_setup_code_block_class %>"><code>gem "logister-ruby", "~> 0.2.8"

Logister.configure do |config|
  config.api_key = "your-project-api-token"
  config.endpoint = "https://your-logister-host.example/api/v1/ingest_events"
  config.repository = ENV["LOGISTER_REPOSITORY"]
  config.commit_sha = ENV["LOGISTER_COMMIT_SHA"]
  config.branch = ENV["LOGISTER_BRANCH"]
  config.capture_request_spans = true
end</code></pre>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
            Public setup guide:
            <%= link_to "Ruby integration docs", docs_site_url(:ruby_integration), target: "_blank", rel: "noopener noreferrer", class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 no-underline font-semibold" %>.
            Package page:
            <%= link_to "RubyGems",
                        "https://rubygems.org/gems/logister-ruby",
                        target: "_blank",
                        rel: "noopener noreferrer",
                        class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 no-underline font-semibold" %>.
          </p>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </article>

    <article class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-5 <%= 'lg:col-span-2' unless @project.owned_by?(current_user) %>">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Ingest endpoint</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">
        POST to
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">/api/v1/ingest_events</code>
        with header
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</code>.
        Accepted ingest requests are limited to 1,200 per minute per API token by default, with retry headers on <code>429</code> responses.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">
        This project uses
        <strong class="text-slate-900"><%= @project.integration_label %></strong>.
        <% if @project.integration_cfml? %>
          Send JSON from Lucee or ColdFusion with `cfhttp`.
        <% elsif @project.integration_python? %>
          Use the <code>logister-python</code> client directly, or add the FastAPI, Django, Flask, or Celery helpers for framework-aware reporting.
        <% elsif @project.integration_dotnet? %>
          Use <code>Logister.AspNetCore</code> for ASP.NET Core middleware, or the base <code>Logister</code> client from workers and services.
        <% elsif @project.integration_javascript? %>
          Use the <code>logister-js</code> client directly, or add the Express middleware if your JavaScript app runs on Express.
        <% elsif @project.integration_cloudflare_pages? %>
          Use direct HTTP telemetry for deployment signals today; the planned Rails importer will pull Cloudflare Pages and Web Analytics metrics.
        <% elsif @project.integration_android? %>
          Install <code>org.logister:logister-android</code> and send mobile telemetry through the Android SDK.
        <% elsif @project.integration_ios? %>
          Add <code>logister-ios</code> with Swift Package Manager and send mobile telemetry through the iOS SDK.
        <% elsif @project.integration_http_api? %>
          Send JSON directly to the HTTP API from any runtime, script, worker, or custom client.
        <% else %>
          Send events through the Ruby gem integration.
        <% end %>
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">
        Request load waterfall charts use <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">event_type: "span"</code>
        payloads with <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">trace_id</code>,
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">span_id</code>,
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">kind</code>, and
        <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800">duration_ms</code>.
      </p>
      <pre class="<%= project_setup_code_block_class %>"><code>{
  "event": {
    "event_type": "error",
    "level": "error",
    "message": "NoMethodError in CheckoutService",
    "fingerprint": "checkout-nomethoderror",
    "occurred_at": "2026-02-14T12:00:00Z",
    "context": { "environment": "production" }
  }
}</code></pre>
    </article>
  </section>
</section>
<% end %>
